The paper deals with natural language processing and specifically with morpheme segmentation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of word representations and syntactico-semantic information suggests the involvement of machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in subfields such as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The validation of the algorithm across datasets suggests a focus on performance evaluation, which is relevant to subfields such as neural networks (cs.NE) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
